The diff viewer, has “**+*“ and “*-**” as a part of the source code line itself, which if copied is quite a nuisance.

Since, the diff status per line is already colour coded with CSS,  pseudo elements can be added via CSS to insert  “**+*“ and “*-*”  prepending the code, without it getting selected. Though, some modifications to the server side also need to be to not insert  “*+*“ and “*-**” .

‌

{code:css}
.refract-container .deletion pre.source::before {
    content: &#x27;-&#x27;;
}

.refract-container .addition pre.source::before {
    content: &#x27;+&#x27;;
}
{code}

Currently, if you want to POST a branch restriction in a repository with a user assignment, you will need to provide the user&#x27;s username.

Branch Restriction API: https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/resource/repositories/%7Busername%7D/%7Brepo_slug%7D/branch-restrictions

{code}
#!CURL

curl -X POST -Lsu usernamea:APP_PASSWORD_OR_PASSWORD -H "Content-Type: application/json" https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/username/repo_name/branch-restrictions --data &#x27;{"groups": [], "kind": "restrict_merges", "pattern": "test", "users": [{"username": "USERNAME_HERE"}]}&#x27;
{code}

However, now that we have GDPR changes when it comes to API endpoints specific to username, user&#x27;s UUID is somehow enforced to be used.

*Feature request*: It would be best if we can allow UUID instead of the username in the API endpoint&#x27;s body request.

{code}
#!CURL

curl -X POST -Lsu usernamea:APP_PASSWORD_OR_PASSWORD -H "Content-Type: application/json" https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/username/repo_name/branch-restrictions --data &#x27;{"groups": [], "kind": "restrict_merges", "pattern": "test", "users": [{"username": "UUID_HERE"}]}&#x27;
{code}

